        <!-- Section: Tax Time Bomb -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-myBlue mb-6">The Second Catastrophe: The Tax Time Bomb</h2>
            
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Let's say you win. You successfully save \$1 Million in your 401(k).
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                You don't have \$1 Million.
                You have a \$1 Million problem.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Your 401(k) or IRA is a <strong>tax-deferred</strong> account. This is a partnership with the government. You saved on taxes up front, but you will pay them on <em>everything</em> you pull out.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                And with national debt soaring, do you believe tax rates will be lower in 10, 15, or 20 years?
            </p>
            
            <!-- Placeholder for an image of a ticking time bomb -->
            <div class="text-center my-8">
                <img src="https://placehold.co/400x300/e0e0e0/555555?text=Ticking+Tax+Bomb" alt="Ticking tax time bomb" class="inline-block rounded-lg shadow-md"
                     onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/400x300/e0e0e0/555555?text=Image+Placeholder'">
            </div>

            <!-- Insight Box -->
            <div class="bg-boxGray border-l-8 border-myBlue rounded-r-lg p-6 my-10 shadow-lg">
                <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-myBlue mb-3">The \$1,000,000 Question:</p>
                <p class="text-xl text-black leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    Which would you rather have?
                </p>
                <ul class="list-none space-y-4">
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed">
                        <strong>A) \$1,000,000 in a 401(k)</strong>, which, after 30% in future taxes, is <strong class="text-2xl text-myRed">\$700,000</strong> to spend.
                    </li>
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed">
                        <strong>B) \$1,000,000 in a "0% Floor" IUL</strong>, which you can access 100% <strong class="text-2xl text-myGreen">tax-free</strong>.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-xl text-black leading-relaxed font-bold mt-6">
                    It's not what you <em>make</em>, it's what you <em>keep</em>.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: Unfair Advantage -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-myBlue mb-6">The "Unfair Advantage": How It Works</h2>
            
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                The "0% Floor" is the engine inside two modern financial vehicles:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-none space-y-4 mb-6">
                <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                    <strong>Fixed Index Annuities (FIAs)</strong>
                </li>
                <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                    <strong>Indexed Universal Life (IUL) policies</strong>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                You are not "in the market." The insurance company credits your account with interest <em>based on</em> a market index (like the S&P 500).
            </p>

            <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">1. When the market goes UP...</p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                You get a portion of the gain, credited as interest. This is often limited by a "Cap" (e.g., 10%). If the market does 25%, you get 10%.
            </p>

            <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">2. When the market goes DOWN...</p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                You get <strong class="text-myGreen text-2xl">0%</strong>. You lose absolutely nothing.
            </p>

            <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">3. This is the "secret":</p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                The next year, you start from your <em>new, higher value</em>. This is called the "Lock & Reset." You are always compounding from your new high point.
            </p>

            <!-- Insight Box -->
            <div class="bg-boxGray border-l-8 border-myBlue rounded-r-lg p-6 my-10 shadow-lg">
                <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-myBlue mb-3">The "Catch" (And Why It's Worth It):</p>
                <p class="text-xl text-black leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    The "catch" is you give up the home-run gains. You'll never get the 30% up-year.
                </p>
                <p class="text-xl text-black leading-relaxed">
                    You are trading <strong>unlimited upside</strong> for <strong>zero downside</strong>. It's a trade retirees are winning every single day.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Section: The Vehicles -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-myBlue mb-6">The Vehicles: IUL vs. FIA</h2>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-8">
                Both use the 0% floor. What's the difference?
            </p>

            <div class="overflow-x-auto shadow-md rounded-lg">
                <table class="w-full text-lg text-left text-gray-700">
                    <thead class="text-lg text-gray-900 bg-gray-200">
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col" class="py-4 px-6">Feature</th>
                            <th scope="col" class="py-4 px-6">FIA (Annuity)</th>
                            <th scope="col" class="py-4 px-6">IUL (Life Insurance)</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody class="bg-white">
                        <tr class="border-b">
                            <td class="py-4 px-6 font-bold">Main Goal</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6">Accumulation & Income</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6"><strong>Tax-Free</strong> Access & Legacy</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b">
                            <td class="py-4 px-6 font-bold">Growth</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6">Tax-Deferred</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6">Tax-Deferred</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b">
                            <td class="py-4 px-6 font-bold">Withdrawals</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6 text-myRed font-bold">Taxed as income</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6 text-myGreen font-bold">Tax-Free (via loans)</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b">
                            <td class="py-4 px-6 font-bold">Legacy</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6 text-myRed">Taxable value</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6 text-myGreen font-bold">Tax-Free Death Benefit</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6 font-bold">Costs</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6">Lower (initially)</td>
                            <td class="py-4 px-6">Higher (includes ins. cost)</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed my-8">
                <strong>An FIA</strong> is a simple, powerful protection tool.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed my-8">
                <strong>An IUL</strong> is a <em>complete</em> retirement strategy that solves for risk, growth, <em>and</em> taxes.
            </p>
        </section>

